The article is a press briefing by Press Secretary Robert Gibbs and Deputy National Security Advisor for Strategic Communications Ben Rhodes on President Obama's trip to Afghanistan. The main purpose of the trip is for the President to thank the troops and civilians for their service during the holiday season. The schedule includes a meeting with President Karzai, a working dinner, and visits to the embassy and wounded soldiers. The article also mentions a review of the Afghanistan strategy that is currently being conducted by the national security staff. The review will assess the progress of the strategy and make any necessary adjustments.